---
description: Request validation belongs in middleware, with field-level messages
globs: apps/api/src/middleware/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Validation

- Validation lives in middleware (e.g. `validateBookPayload`), NOT in route handlers.
- On failure, `next(new ValidationError(message, details))` — let the error handler respond.
- `ValidationError`'s `details` is a field-keyed object of messages:
  `{ title: "title is required", year: "year must be an integer between 1000 and 2027" }`.
- Collect ALL field errors in one pass, then return them together — don't fail on the first.
- After validating, normalize `req.body` to the typed payload (trim strings, coerce numbers)
  so downstream services receive clean, typed input.
